body: If I understood correctly your question, and the third lib is our C# API, then you could develop something similar to it. Most of the API is exported via a table (struct) of C function pointers. You can't call C++ directly though, only via C entry points.

body:
> so it can't call onnxruntime DLL of c++ ? only by compiling the csharp version, and develop with csharp version onnxruntime? even i export the c++ functional interface by extern "C" declaration？ @yuslepukhin

You can call any DLL from C# using exported C entry points, the fact it is written in C++ or any other language becomes irrelevant. You can use some of the examples in our C# API. However, I recommend extensive reading of C# documentation.
